Habitat. Collected in various aquatic habitats, mostly larger pools both natural and manmade (e.g. Figs 2 , 14 ); frequently attracted also to light traps. In the Arabian Peninsula so far not documented from higher altitudes.

Distribution.
Cybister tripuncatus
occurs in subtropical and tropical areas of the whole Old World. The subspecies
C. t. africanus
occurs in entire continental Africa, reaching south Europe in the north and Arabian Peninsula in the east ( GUIGNOT 1961 ).
